SIMPLE: lead-free
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: lead-free
<hw>lead-free</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>not containing the
element lead.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>specifically:</specif> <def>Not containing a lead
additive such as tetraethyllead or tetramethyllead; -- of gasoline;
<as>as, Most modern cars run on <ex>lead-free</ex> gasoline</as>.
Oposite of <ant>leaded</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nonleaded, unleaded.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>specifically:</specif> <def>Not containing a
pigment having lead as a component; -- of paints; <as>as,
<ex>lead-free</ex> paint should be used wherever children are exposed to
the painted surface</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Leadhillite</ent>⟦br⟧
